<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Sk's and Pala's the eternal struggle....</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?holydevil">holydevil</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:36 a.m. 20/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Sk's and Pala's the eternal struggle....<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1091" TARGET=_self>Sk's and Pala's the eternal struggle....</A> (Novandamis)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Whats really dum,b is that sk have some of these spells its a damn shadow night, why the hell should it need invisblilty from undead? Undead shouldn't attack them in the first place, and I am sure that one of the last things a sk would hunt, undead should just not attack shadow knights its realitisc, and instead of giving them those useless spells mayeb you could give them more useful ones, but all these protection from undead spells that a shadow night has is just stupid.

<P>&gt; Okay I have played both a sk and a paladin and have come to this
<BR>&gt; conclusion. Everything about both of them is perfect except for
<BR>&gt; a few spells on the sk side of the battle. In regards to
<BR>&gt; 'trademark' spells ( such as the clerics minor, lesser, and
<BR>&gt; healing, or the wizards burn spells or necro's life suck spells,
<BR>&gt; i refer to as 'trademark' spells) the paladin has all of the
<BR>&gt; clerics trademark spells such as minor healing, courage cure
<BR>&gt; poison, yaulp, which are pretty much all the good or i should
<BR>&gt; say most used spells from that spell level, yes there are others
<BR>&gt; he has that are good but this isn't my point. My point is on the
<BR>&gt; other side of the fence the sk doesn't get a 'trademark' spell
<BR>&gt; untiul level 22, vampiric embrace. I realize that they get a
<BR>&gt; summon pet spell but that doesn't happen until level 15 and he
<BR>&gt; gets the level 8 necro spell bone walk. So tell me when I am
<BR>&gt; fightin a level 12 to 16 creature when I am level 15 how much
<BR>&gt; good do you think that level 8 or 9 skel is gonna do? Some of
<BR>&gt; you are saying well he might hit them and do a little damage or
<BR>&gt; take a little bit of the heat off me but what happens when I am
<BR>&gt; level 21 ( i dont get different spells until level 22) and I
<BR>&gt; have a level 8 or 9 skel, well I dont even have to say it. Sorry
<BR>&gt; if my post comes off argumentative I just dont want people to
<BR>&gt; try and argue that I am wrong. The point of my post is to
<BR>&gt; suggest that the sk for sure be given lifetap at level 9 instead
<BR>&gt; of some less used spell like sense the dead or what have you and
<BR>&gt; at level 15 be given lifespike instead of fear or numb dead or
<BR>&gt; whatever. The next suggestion is that 1 of 2 things happen with
<BR>&gt; pets and sk's as they are very near worthless now. #1 the level
<BR>&gt; 8 bone walk at 15 become the level 12 convoke shadow( at least
<BR>&gt; the pet is closer to your level for a little while:( and so on
<BR>&gt; or #2 the sk be given beef up offensively spells (like the
<BR>&gt; shaman inner fire and such)instead of summon pet spells because
<BR>&gt; the pala has all of the best beef up defensively spells that the
<BR>&gt; cleric gets such as courage at 9, holy armor at 15 and center at
<BR>&gt; 22. Or they could simply give the sk minor eilding, lesser
<BR>&gt; sheilding , and stuff like that. As it stands in my eyes the sk
<BR>&gt; is noticeably weaker in the spells area than the paladin. I
<BR>&gt; would like more than a agree or disagree post from the board. I
<BR>&gt; would like to hear a response from someone who could possibly
<BR>&gt; change this and tell me why that they arent doing it IF the
<BR>&gt; answer is no. Or someone like geiger or the black who has actual
<BR>&gt; contact with the gm's. THX a million guys.
<P>&gt; Novandamis
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
